        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 12 at 5:28PM MDT by NWS Glasgow MT</headline>
        <description>At 528 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Redstone, or 16 miles west of Plentywood, moving northeast at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and small hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Redstone and Archer.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
